				<note resp="Philip Lampi">The Congressional election was directly influenced by that for State Senate at least in Huntington and Mifflin counties, where a well know Federalist was running against a Republican. So since the Federalists were running a candidate for State Senate, their votes were split between the various candidates for Congress. In Centre County it seems the Federalist voted for John Brown, while in Huntington for Robert Allison and in Mifflin, for Robert Allison and John Mitchell.</note>
